00:44:38.940 --> 00:44:44.260
I wouldn't necessarily say that I tried anything before because the whole thing was completely unintentional.

00:44:44.590 --> 00:44:48.460
I mean, I basically bought myself a 3D printer in late 2012.

00:44:49.440 --> 00:44:52.920
I wanted to be able to put it in my spare bathroom and monitor it from afar,

00:44:53.380 --> 00:44:56.200
because back then this thing was tying up my PC.

00:44:56.390 --> 00:45:00.680
You had to constantly keep it connected so it could operate and that for hours and hours.

00:45:00.790 --> 00:45:02.760
And it made noises and it produced fumes.

00:45:02.850 --> 00:45:04.900
And I just wanted it out of my office.

00:45:06.160 --> 00:45:13.620
And to be able to play games on my PC again, instead of having it, yeah, basically communicate constantly with a 3D printer.

00:45:14.520 --> 00:45:22.460
And so I bought myself a Raspberry Pi and I was looking online for something to be able to just put on this Pi and attach to the printer and throw a Wi-Fi dongle in.

00:45:22.540 --> 00:45:24.520
Because back then the Pi didn't have Wi-Fi built in.

00:45:25.120 --> 00:45:27.500
And throw that in the spare bathroom, but there wasn't anything.

00:45:27.840 --> 00:45:32.480
So over the course of my Christmas break in 2012, I sat down and changed that.

00:45:32.740 --> 00:45:35.060
And this is basically the origin story of Octoprint.

00:45:35.240 --> 00:45:36.960
I just wanted to scratch my own itch.

00:45:36.970 --> 00:45:39.120
I wanted to put my printer in my spare bathroom.

00:45:39.440 --> 00:45:39.920
This is all.

00:45:40.520 --> 00:45:44.400
And apparently a lot of people had the same problem because I just, you know,

00:45:44.560 --> 00:45:46.740
like how we like to do these things.

00:45:46.790 --> 00:45:48.820
We build something that we think might be interesting.

00:45:48.910 --> 00:45:53.100
We throw it up on GitHub and go just like here, go nuts, enjoy,

00:45:53.500 --> 00:45:54.220
have fun with that.

00:45:54.480 --> 00:45:57.240
And I suddenly started getting emails from all around the world.

00:45:57.500 --> 00:45:58.900
Like, hey, I have this in this printer.

00:45:59.010 --> 00:46:00.540
Can you also make it work with that?

00:46:00.760 --> 00:46:05.080
